ObjectBox just supports storing [some base types by default][1]. For custom types you have to either [map them to a supported type][2], or I assume what you are looking for in this case [create a relation][3] to an `@Entity` class:

    @Entity()
    class Set {
      int? id;
      final exercise = ToOne&lt;Exercise&gt;();
      final int? repetitions;
    }

    // To change the ToOne target:
    set.exercise.target = Exercise();


  [1]: https://docs.objectbox.io/advanced/custom-types
  [2]: https://docs.objectbox.io/advanced/custom-types#convert-annotation-and-property-converter
  [3]: https://docs.objectbox.io/relations

